  "reviews": [
    {
      "author": "MovieGuys",
      "content": "Colony is a marginal departure from your classic zombie flick. While intelligently written, there's not a lot on offer here, aside from a zombie hive mind proposition, that distinguishes this outbreak zombie horror disaster drama from others in the genre. That's not to say it's not worth a look if you like this kind of thing. The acting is excellent; the characters have a genuine depth, offering up predictably human responses, for better or worse, to the unfolding disaster that befalls them. Action is solid too, with lots of zombie thrills but little in the way of genuine scares, backed by solid choregraphy and cinamatics. \r\n\r\nIn summary. Colony isn't doing anything overly new, but its script offers enough interest and excitement to make this film a worthwhile watch.",
      "rating": 7,
      "createdAt": "2026-06-16T23:16:22Z"
    }
  ],
